This paper is about neural language models and their ability to represent constituent-level features, specifically using coordinated noun phrases as a case study. This topic falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP), which is typically classified under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of neural networks, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of large corpora, which could fall under neural networks (cs.NE) or computer vision (cs.CV) if the corpora includes image data. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CV, in that order.
